title: Kendra Reynolds
text:
Kendra Reynolds (born ) is a New Zealand <a href="rugby%20union">rugby union</a> player. She is a <a href="Flanker%20%28rugby%20union%29">flanker</a> and made her debut for the New Zealand national women's side, the <a href="New%20Zealand%20women%27s%20national%20rugby%20union%20team">Black Ferns</a>, against <a href="France%20women%27s%20national%20rugby%20union%20team">France</a> in 2021.
Career.
Reynolds played for the New Zealand Development XV at the <a href="2019%20Oceania%20Rugby%20Women%27s%20Championship">2019 Oceania Rugby Women's Championship</a> in Fiji. She made her provincial debut for <a href="Waikato%20Rugby%20Union">Waikato</a> in 2012, before moving to <a href="Bay%20of%20Plenty">Bay of Plenty</a> in 2014 and playing for the Volcanix.
Reynolds was named in the <a href="Chiefs%20%28rugby%20union%29%23Women%27s%20team">Chiefs Manawa</a> squad for the inaugural <a href="Super%20Rugby%20Aupiki">Super Rugby Aupiki</a> season for 2022.
